*** Current bugs ***
Issue: After having the calculator solve an equation, it can't properly solve again when another part of an equation is added
Steps to reproduce: 
	1. Solve an equation (don't clear the calculator) 
	2. Add 1 or more operators and values after the answer to create another equation
	3. Attempt to solve for the new quation, an incorrect answer will be outputted
Cause: Order of operations is wrong due to the previously inputted values still being stored in the input ArrayList (new system to store values needed?)
	
Issue: Nodes do not resize themselves when the window is resized
Steps to reproduce:
	1. Open the GUI application
	2. Resize the window with the cursor or fullscreen button, nodes will not adjust their size to match the resolution of the window
Cause: Not a default functionality of JavaFX nodes (do node objects have a property to control this?).

Issue: Equations cannot be solved when entered via typing into the TextField 
Steps to reproduce: 
	1. Enter an equation into the TextField by selecting it and then typing on the keyboard
	2. "error, no operation selected" will appear in the Textfield and. Either the clearbutton or a number button must be pressed for the calculator to function again
Cause: TextField used String values while the Input ArrayList uses wrapper Double values (how does conversion work between them?).

Issue: Equations with two or more distinct operators cannot be solved properly
Steps to reproduce:
	1. Enter an equation that contains 2 distinct operators
	2. The outputted answer will be incorrect
Cause: Order of operations is wrong due to the previously inputted values still being stored in the input ArrayList (new system to store values needed?)

Issue: Values still be entered side by side without an operator seperating them
Steps to reproduce:
	1. Use the number buttons to enter 2 or more numbers without entering an operator between them
	2. The numbers will display side by side, "no operation" error will not appear until the equals method is used
Cause: The check for preventing this is not present outside of the areas of code where attempts are made to solve the equation
